image_desc: Photo by Joyce Lye 赖玉珠 on December 10, 2020. May be an image of 2 people, hair and people standing.
text:
“How nice if I can join the Sangha group of Tzu Chi in Hualian, Taiwan.” That was my thought when my hair was shaved in 2015. Even though, my intention then was to raise $50,000 for the Compassion Support Scheme for cancer patients of all age groups. 

This year , I have just completed my 3-km daily walk from home to my office at Aljunied Crescent for 151 days during 2020 Cut Cut Cut - Cut For Compassion event. For every km I'd walked, I raised $10 for Kampung Senang. I was very reluctant to walk since becoming a mum 30 years ago, and would rely on driving even for a distance of just 2 km. A friend of donkey years challenged me by pledging a donation of $ 10 per km to Kampung Senang if I could walk to work and reduce carbon emission.

This year, besides walking a distance of 453 km , I have set the event target higher at $80,000 due to increased needs of people affected by both mental health issues and chronic illnesses. So far, we've raised only $41,000. If we can find donors for an additional $40,000, I have promised to shave my hair again. 

I sincerely hope to keep that promise.
https://www.kampungsenang.org/compassion-fund/

With Covid-19 on a rampage, many of us are at the end of our tethers, ready to fly off our handles. Frustration is nationwide at best, and suffocation is an understatement for many of us deprived of roaming our frequent haunts with the people we love. 😩😩😩⁣
⁣
Altogether, the year has been an overwhelmingly dark one for billions of people all over the world. While that is the reality, this is also a reality : 𝘞𝘦 𝘨𝘦𝘵 𝘵𝘰 𝘤𝘩𝘰𝘰𝘴𝘦 𝘵𝘰 𝘚𝘦𝘦 𝘛𝘩𝘦 𝘓𝘪𝘨𝘩𝘵. 🌟🌟🌟⁣
⁣
Despite the terrible hand that we have been dealt with, we get to choose to play our cards the best way we can. Despite the storm of death and destruction that the virus has brought, we get to choose to see the very best of humanity - our frontline heroes - resilient and resolved in this fight. 𝘋𝘦𝘴𝘱𝘪𝘵𝘦 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘥𝘢𝘳𝘬𝘯𝘦𝘴𝘴, we get to choose to see the good in whatever situation we are in.⁣
⁣

image_desc: Photo by Muiee メイ on December 29, 2020. May be an image of food.
text:
年末のシンガポールは風が強い、雨が降った後は気温が一気に23-24度に下がり、かなり寒いです😨 こんな日は暖かい料理が食べたい気分❣️

今日の夕食はインドネシア風の甘酸味調味料Masak Merahをチキン、トマト、茄子とじゃがいも入りの煮物にしました〜スープは多目にして、残りのRussian Bread と一緒に食べました〜😋 寒い日はやはり身体がポカポカになる料理だね❣️

YouTubeで生食パンをホームベーカリーで作るレシピを見て〜丁度生クリームが有り、試しに作りました😆 

ホームベーカリーで生地を捏ね+２次発酵、生地を出し食パン型に入れ、2/3分の高さまで発酵したら、オーブンに入れ180度15分>160度15分で焼き上がり❣️

綺麗な食パンが初めて焼けて〜🍞…めちゃ嬉しい😆 
しかも食感がふわふわでモッチリ〜美味しい❣️
生クリーム入りでこんな食パン🍞が出来るとは…
素晴らしいです❣️これから我が家の定番にしよう👌

皆さん良い日を❣️Stay Safe & Healthy 

年末的季候風 風特別大
由其雨后 气溫下降 冷風颼颼 
这时候吃热乎乎的食物 最棒了！
晚餐煮了一鍋用印尼式的Masak Merah 调味酱
燜煮半只鸡、番茄、马铃薯和茄子 再搭配剩余的罗宋面包 
簡單又美味 身心也暖起來了～❤️

前阵子从Youtube见到日式吐司 🍞 的recipe 
面团要加入Whipped cream 
刚好冰箱还剩不少whipped cream 就取之試試
用bread maker进行Kneading 和二次發酵
取出放进吐司模型 再继续犮酵至兩倍
接著进烤箱烘焙 没想到居然初次可以烤到这么美 👍
让我惊讶 也太棒了👏
原來加whipped cream後的吐司 口感是这么软松 
口感好像在日本吃到的吐司🍞那样❗️
賛！決定列入家常面包名單中❣️

㊗️大家 幸福平安 Happy Holidays

image_desc: Photo by 🌹Yvaine • 欣🎀 on December 29, 2020. May be a closeup of 1 person and hair.
text:
#throwbackto #may2020 #欣2020爱你爱妳 #circuitbreakersg 

Pictured here with make up and in work formal attire; this was the new norm; getting dressed up at home and having interviews/meetings via zoom. This was like the don't know how many interviews i had, after sending in hundreds of job applications. End of interviews responses were almost similar; "We do not know when we can be back in office, we will still be in touch with you again.".

***

One of my resolutions for 2020 was to get back to workforce after my long hiatus of being out of the working society.

When i first made the decision to be a homemaker 7 years back, i wasn't expecting myself to be "out" for so long.

All these years, i did try to "get out" of my own current circumstances. It wasn't easy as kids' well-being and matters are always on mind; not easy to let go of a lot when I've been so hands-on with them.

In 2016, i finally stepped out and did some job searching. Was delighted that i managed to get a job offered not long after. However, we had an accidental blessing when I found out i was pregnant with #babygirl, before i signed the offer contract. Employer wasn't accepting towards my pregnancy; pretty much expected; my job offer was withdrawn.

Oh wells... Here comes another year(s) of homemaking life.

After giving birth in 2017, i decided that i should complete my degree prior to going back to workforce; at least i could have a nice portfolio as i upgraded myself during my hiatus off working society.

Another year and two passed; i finished my last paper in Dec 2018 while full-time caring for the youngest at home. Woohoo! So much effort and commitment. I finally made it.

2019 came along and i thot "yeah yeah!"; No obstruction for me to get a job. Was so looking forward.

As #bigboy advanced into his next stage of life, i thot i can settle him a little first before i start and focus more on job searching. Who knew just into the first Saturday of 2019, i had that freaky accident at home that left me handicapped for a few months. WHAT! Then physical destruction from head to toes came subsequently; caused by the effect of medications, x-rays etc etc.

text:
昨晩焼いたRussian Bread を朝食に❣️シンガポールのベーカリーにあんまりかほぼ見かけないRussian Bread, マレーシア、台湾や香港のベーカリーには良く買えるんですが、何故かシンガポールでは見えない😂 中国語では”羅宋麵包” と呼んで、その羅宋は上海語発音のRussian から❗️なるほど〜ロシアの赤いボロシチスープも”羅宋湯”と呼んでいて……やっと謎が解けた❗️😆

作り方はそんなに難しく無いが、色んなレシピが有り、今回はシンプルバージョンから試しました〜食感がふわふわで上のバター🧈が香ばしい〜旦那氏も👍 次はサクサク感をしたRussian Breadを作りたいです❣️

昨晩の夕食はSpinach Mushroom Pizza 
キャストアイロンのフライパンで焼くピザは生地がサクサクして美味しい❣️

皆さん良い日を❣️2020年もそろそろ終わり〜Stay Safe & Healthy 💪

昨晚烤好的罗宋面包 🥖

说到罗宋面包 我和老爷都喜歡 然而在這里的Bakery
很难买到 以前越提去JB 很常在Lavendar Bakery买回來 
昨天想到这面包 查看做法後 就試試 
Shaping 还需要多进步 😂 手残 型做的不好
不過味道有像  這recipe 罗宋面包口感是软的 
还不錯  下次试用汤种的方法 

PS: 原来罗宋是上海发音的俄罗斯🇷🇺 😂 又長知识了
难怪以前在马来西亚买这个面包时 奇怪怎么叫罗宋 
那个俄罗斯有名的红红Borcsht 汤 也叫罗宋汤  一直不解
原来是发音的称呼呀！我那多年的谜题 终于解开了～ 😂

text:
When the fringe looks like drawn curtains in the mornings 🙄 
你们喝水了吗？ 

#throwback #circuitbreakersg #cutmyownbangs

When the entire world goes into a holiday frenzy, it feels as if we cannot be anything but happy. 🥲⁣
⁣
We are bombarded with ads of smiling families feasting on Christmas goodies, our social media feeds are filled to the brim with festive greetings, and holiday music seems to blare from every available loudspeaker. ⁣
⁣
Everyone seems so 𝘨𝘳𝘢𝘵𝘦𝘧𝘶𝘭 and 𝘵𝘩𝘢𝘯𝘬𝘧𝘶𝘭, and it feels almost sinful not to partake in the celebrations wholeheartedly. ⁣
⁣
But, we know that isn’t the reality. ⁣
⁣
For some of us, the holidays are a great source of pain - a sobering reminder of 𝐛𝐫𝐨𝐤𝐞𝐧 𝐝𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐦𝐬, 𝐫𝐞𝐥𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧𝐬𝐡𝐢𝐩𝐬, 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐟𝐚𝐦𝐢𝐥𝐢𝐞𝐬. To others, it is the absence of what once was. Sometimes, the grandness of the  hustle and bustle makes us feel small and insignificant; a lonely blink amidst a vast backdrop.👤 ⁣
⁣
2020 has been 𝘲𝘶𝘪𝘵𝘦 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘺𝘦𝘢𝘳 hasn’t it? ⁣
⁣
As the year comes to a close, this is a reminder that we are not alone. No matter how dark the year has been, there are people who know too well the struggles you go through.⁣
 ⁣
You are 𝘯𝘰𝘵 𝘢𝘭𝘰𝘯𝘦. ❤⁣
⁣

Each artwork consists of long exposure of exactly one hour, and a multi-exposure of 60 photographs taken every 60 seconds over the same hour.'.
text:
Happy publication day to @wwyart’s Pandemic Time!
A collaborative project that brings together 24 poets working in Singapore to write through each hour of the day in response to time, which has become innumerable in this ridiculous year. As the first poem I’ve had published in Singapore, it’s a delight and a privilege to be included here alongside friends.

The poems and recordings are available at https://pandemictime.org.

image_desc: Photo shared by Cheng Wei May Lee on December 25, 2020 tagging @pix_story. May be an image of 2 people, hair, biceps, people standing and text that says 'BRING THE SHOW'.
text:
Every Friday, I go for #torturewithleonard , and if I am lucky enough to book a #bodybalance slot, #fridaywithsean (though often he manages to make it #torturewithsean with some crazy Pilates) Two completely different workouts, but I always feel so good and ready for the weekend after. Glad I was able to do both on this Christmas Day and last Friday of 2020!

This year, I totally changed my mindset towards keeping fit and have found more enjoyment and fulfilllment from my time in the gym / working out more than ever. For the first time in my life (and especially after lockdown during #circuitbreakersg), I try to give attention to various aspects of fitness- cardio, strength, core, balance, flexibility etcetc (albeit not at all equal).

Sometimes, I feel bad that I can no longer run 10km daily & 21km whenever I feel like it, but in some ways, I have gained much more!

Everyone says I’m lucky to be so “fit” because I could run everyday (slowly)- disciplined and stubborn maybe, but definitely not fit! When I was 30, I couldn’t even do five burpees, hold a plank or jump up a bench! 

Everyone starts somewhere, and fitness is just a continuous journey you do for your mind and body, and most importantly, for yourself. 

In the coming year(s), I want to add my “finger fitness” back to my regime- started the Christmas morning listening to Debussy and then practicing the piano arrangement of Grieg’s Holberg Suite on, and it was wonderful. 

#Merry Christmas! @pix_story @sean_bmf @fitnessfirstsg #tgif

𝘒𝘪𝘯𝘵𝘴𝘶𝘨𝘪, also known as Kintsukuroi,  is the Japanese art of restoring broken pottery with lacquered resin and powdered gold.⁣
⁣
The beauty of Kintsugi lies in its unapologetic display of each and every imperfection. They are displayed proudly in gold, and not hidden away. Each piece passes through masterful hands in the restoration process, and every fracture and flaw is honoured as a testament to its rich history.⁣
⁣
The resulting masterpieces are uniquely beautiful, and risen in value.⁣
⁣
Brokenness - that is one thing we all have in common. We all live with some form of brokenness - broken hearts, shattered dreams, crushed hopes, failing friendships or splintered families. ⁣
⁣
We shy away from our flaws and imperfections, desperately keeping them away from the light of day. We keep them hidden and stored away in the lockers of our hearts. We regard them as weaknesses that could be exploited if we happen to let the walls, that we have put up to keep us safe, down.⁣
⁣
Perhaps the scars we all bear are the greatest sources of our strength. Perhaps our imperfections are indicators that we are not programmed robots. Perhaps our brokenness is but a reminder - that we are living and breathing despite the pain.⁣
Perhaps everything beautiful, brilliant, and gorgeous about us  is not only found in what we are comfortable with showing, but also in the imperfections and scars we choose to hide.⁣
⁣
There is 𝐛𝐞𝐚𝐮𝐭𝐲 𝐢𝐧 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐛𝐫𝐨𝐤𝐞𝐧.⁣

image_desc: Photo shared by ONEおね Patisserie on December 23, 2020 tagging @one.o.nepatisserie.
text:
𝓒𝓱𝓻𝓲𝓼𝓽𝓶𝓪𝓼 🎄𝓔𝓿𝓮. Are you organized & ready for gatherings? ⛄️

It’s been an interesting 2020, many are able to celebrate this end of year on a positive note as we welcome Phase 3 😌

It’s been a heartening period running this home business as we handmake each cake and helped many gift their loved ones with sweet messages. Here’s reviewing this unique year with some pictures. Have you gotten any of these? 

We started this biz in April 2020 as the world flustered & Singapore going into 𝘊𝘪𝘳𝘤𝘶𝘪𝘵 𝘉𝘳𝘦𝘢𝘬𝘦𝘳 with several rules and restrictions for home biz. 

In May, we had small dessert boxes gifted with many many “𝘚𝘵𝘢𝘺 𝘚𝘢𝘧𝘦” messages to encourage their family and friends amidst the uncertainty during 𝘊𝘪𝘳𝘤𝘶𝘪𝘵 𝘉𝘳𝘦𝘢𝘬𝘦𝘳. (𝘗𝘪𝘤 2)

When 𝘗𝘩𝘢𝘴𝘦 1 arrived in June, Dessert Boxes & ChiffONE Boxes were gifted by corporate & friends with “𝘑𝘪𝘢𝘺𝘰𝘶” messages. Many are still WFH...cabin fever and mental health awareness increases as we had been staying at home! (𝘗𝘪𝘤 3 & 4)

We were very thankful to be featured on 𝑻𝒉𝒆 𝑺𝒕𝒓𝒂𝒊𝒕𝒔 𝑻𝒊𝒎𝒆𝒔 for our limited edition 𝑵𝒂𝒕𝒊𝒐𝒏𝒂𝒍 𝑫𝒂𝒚 Specials!  It was tediously great fun to create our 🇸🇬 flag with 🍓 ! (𝘗𝘪𝘤 5) 

Since Sep, as more return to offices (yay or nay 🤣), 𝘾𝙝𝙞𝙛𝙛𝙊𝙉𝙀 𝘽𝙤𝙭𝙚𝙨 continue to be very popular as many love to try all flavors! We individually wrap each slice for easy pantry-food in office! (𝘗𝘪𝘤 4). 

There are many Sep, Oct & Nov babies... or is it that small gatherings are finally allowed? Rose Chiffon cakes is loved for being a light cake but our Strawberry Fresh Cream Cake is the most popular for birthdays!  And what if our customer love both our rose & strawberry cake...we had a customized 𝑺𝒕𝒓𝒂𝒘𝒃𝒆𝒓𝒓𝒚 & 𝑹𝒐𝒔𝒆 𝑭𝒓𝒆𝒔𝒉 𝑪𝒓𝒆𝒂𝒎 𝑪𝒂𝒌𝒆! (𝘗𝘪𝘤 6). Will you like to try it too? 

Mulled Wine is “the 🎄 drink” for me and family, and what’s better than creating 𝑴𝒖𝒍𝒍𝒆𝒅 𝑾𝒊𝒏𝒆 𝑳𝒐𝒈 𝑪𝒂𝒌𝒆? (𝘗𝘪𝘤 7)

Our Christmas Special has to have our signature too, 𝑺𝒕𝒓𝒂𝒘𝒃𝒆𝒓𝒓𝒚 𝑭𝒓𝒆𝒔𝒉 𝑪𝒓𝒆𝒂𝒎 𝑳𝒐𝒈 𝑪𝒂𝒌𝒆! (𝘗𝘪𝘤 8)

Thankful for all the support. 

𝓜𝓮𝓻𝓻𝔂 𝓒𝓱𝓻𝓲𝓼𝓽𝓶𝓪𝓼 !

text:
“The same light you see in others is shining within you, too” - Morgan Harper Nichols

Everyone has a story to tell, and everyone has a light to shine- including you. 📖

Sometimes you have to show up and realise that your very presence is the light that another sees. Even when you feel the total opposite, there is a light that shines brightly and beautifully in you.🌟🌟🌟

Even in the darkest of nights, the light that shines in you is as sure as the rising sun. You are stronger than you think, and infinitely worth more than you believe to the people around you.

As you See The Light in others, know this: the people around you See The light in you too.

image_desc: Photo by Harrie - The Bichon Frisé 🐑🐶 on December 22, 2020. May be an image of Maltese.
text:
Do you believe in dog angels 🐶👼🏻? Dog is god spelled backwards, and it’s not hard to see why.

Harrie came home with us on 9 March 2002 and became part of our family for 6,658 days till the day he left us forever on 31 May 2020. He waited faithfully for his owner hooman to wake up on the following morning before breathing his last with a smile on his angelic face. A fluffy bichon frisé shaped cloud ☁️ appeared in the sky shortly after his departure on 31 May. After his memorial on 1 Jun, Harrie crossed the rainbow bridge as a beautiful 🌈 formed in the sky after the rain shower 🌧, leading to an auburn sunset 🌅 which also marked the end of the Circuit Breaker period. The sky turned spectacularly dramatic next early morning, followed by a couple of bichon clouds in the first few months.

- Playmate hooman, Brenda
.
.
.
.
.

image_desc: Photo by INONE Story in Singapore. May be an image of text that says 'SEE THE LIGHT'.
text:
Sometimes, we find ourselves in a pit without the strength to get out of, where a deep darkness blankets over us and hope is the last thing on our minds. That smothering darkness seems to overwhelm us to the point of physical and mental exhaustion.🤦🏽‍♂️🤦🏽‍♂️🤦🏽‍♂️⁣⁣
⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Beginning to search for an ever-elusive light in a dire situation like this seems much too effortful. We might even ask “𝘞𝘩𝘢𝘵’𝘴 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘱𝘰𝘪𝘯𝘵 𝘪𝘯 𝘢𝘭𝘭 𝘰𝘧 𝘵𝘩𝘪𝘴? 𝘞𝘩𝘺 𝘴𝘩𝘰𝘶𝘭𝘥 𝘐 𝘭𝘪𝘷𝘦?”⁣⁣
⁣⁣
⁣⁣
But what if all we needed to do is open our eyes and realise that 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐫𝐚𝐲 𝐨𝐟 𝐥𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭 𝐡𝐚𝐬 𝐛𝐞𝐞𝐧 𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐫𝐞 𝐚𝐥𝐥 𝐚𝐥𝐨𝐧𝐠? It is found in the people who love you, care for you, and who you mean the world to.❤️🫂❤️⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣
𝐒𝐞𝐞 𝐓𝐡𝐞 𝐋𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭 is a reminder that even on your worst days, there is a reason to live. 𝐘𝐨𝐮 𝐚𝐫𝐞 𝐧𝐞𝐯𝐞𝐫 𝐚𝐥𝐨𝐧𝐞. 𝐘𝐨𝐮 𝐦𝐞𝐚𝐧 𝐬𝐨 𝐦𝐮𝐜𝐡 𝐦𝐨𝐫𝐞 𝐭𝐨 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐩𝐞𝐨𝐩𝐥𝐞 𝐚𝐫𝐨𝐮𝐧𝐝 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐭𝐡𝐚𝐧 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐥𝐢𝐬𝐞.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
As the year comes to a close, and as 2021 beckons on the horizon, I hope you know that the light has been there all along. Look up, 𝐨𝐩𝐞𝐧 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐞𝐲𝐞𝐬, and 𝐒𝐞𝐞 𝐓𝐡𝐞 𝐋𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭.🌟🌟🌟

image_desc: Photo by Muiee メイ on December 20, 2020. May be an image of 1 person and food.
text:
やっとシンガポールにも天丼てんやが来ました❗️バンコクより数年も遅れましたが何よりです🤣

東京都内の駅で良く見かける天丼てんや、以前お勤めしたIT会社で東京出張へのムスリム同僚達が食事処を聴く度に、天丼てんやを紹介しました〜その後彼等が毎度東京行くたびに天丼てんやが定番になり🤣 凄くお気に入りらしい〜

ちょと前に旦那氏とオーチャドへ買い物、早めの晩餐を天丼てんやで食べました〜上天丼と鶏天丼を注文し、天ぷらはサクサクして美味しいですが…お米がもちもちしなくて、つゆをかけたご飯は挟む度お箸から落ちる…パサパサしてアジアのお米使用？🤔

カウンターで青森県産米まっしぐらの表紙が見えて、調べると…お米は硬めで、粘り気が少ない、一粒一粒しっかりが特徴…初耳❗️なるほど〜だから食感がアジア米に似ているんだ😲

ちょと少し物足りない晩餐でしたが……🤣
天丼は美味しかったです♪
近くに天丼を食べるお店が無いので
食べたい時は都会に行かないと…😭

皆さん良い日を❣️Stay Safe & Healthy

10月開幕的日本平價連鎖店天丼てんや
日本各車站或商场内 很常見的平价天丼店
我們在東京住宿淺草區時 也常去光顧
好幾年前在曼谷的Siam Square 2 
天丼てんや己進駐 也光顧過
虽然有点迟 新加坡终于进驻了！
点了上天丼和鸡天丼 还不錯吃
只是饭不粘 淋了酱汁的米粒变得很散  夾不起來 
饭粒不大粘 無法和炸物夾着一起享用 
感覺有点吃不飽 😫  明明在東京吃 一碗就飽 奇怪？
后来付款时见贴着使用青森产的まっしぐら米种
上网查一下 其米的特征是不大粘 口感比较硬 难怪！
整体来说这里的天丼还是不错吃！

㊗️大家 生活愉快！平安幸福 🙏.

image_desc: Photo by Janie Chua on December 20, 2020. May be an image of 1 person, child, standing and christmas tree.
text:
Swimming Sundays. Last swim class of the year.

Can’t believe we made it through this challenging year without skipping a single week of swim lessons at @swishswimming. That’s not counting the weeks during the #circuitbreakersg and #postcircuitbreakersg Phase 1 when everything was shut, of course. I still remember how disappointed Isaac was back then when he had to stay home with zero pool time. 

Thank goodness that’s all behind us now. It’s great to see him having some pre and post class fun with the dancing reindeer and Christmas tree, and of course, his favourite Aunty Liza.

@_.n1z._ #superbaby #baby아이 #29monthsold #weekendshenanigans #sundayfunday #christmasiscoming #myfavouritetimeoftheyear #whenisaacsmiles #shopmonbebesg

text:
Congratulations to @jingkangjk and @leexinyi_van !!
It’s been such a blessing & privilege to work with you guys and witness the wedding prep journey🧡🥰.

image_desc: Photo by Muiee メイ on December 17, 2020. May be an image of food.
text:
.
近所のモールに珍しく中国のハラル店がオープン❗️ 
中国北西部 甘粛省蘭州の郷土料理でイスラム教の少数民族
が受け継いできたハラル料理の一種”蘭州牛肉麺” 🍜 

“舌尖尖”(Tongue Tip) は蘭州で有名来なその一軒
来星一年半だけどもう4店舗をオープンしています
ローカルのムスリム方もお店で食事をしていました

蘭州牛肉麵と言えばスープは塩味がベース
初めて食べるので一応ブランド牛肉麺、酸菜牛肉麵
両方に辛子入りを頼みました

スープが溢れるほどに具材も見えない牛肉麺〜😂
私にとっては少し塩っぽいスープですが
辛子を混ぜると味が一段アップされ…この味はいける👍 
現場で作る麺は歯ごたえが有りツルツルして〜
これは美味しかったわ❣️ 特に細麺が一番お勧めです〜

近处的商场 新开了一家来自甘肃省兰州市 
拥有中国兰州牛肉面认证 著名的兰州牛肉拉面品牌之一
“舌尖尖兰州牛肉面”(Tongue Tip Lanzou Beef Noodles) 
之前经过见不少回教徙来用餐 就偕老爷一起来光顾
点了招牌牛肉面和酸菜牛肉面 加辣子
端上來的牛肉面 湯多到要漏出来了……😳
牛肉在那？酸菜在那？被汤淹未...卖相有點不佳 
先試一口清汤 对我來說有点咸 
但把辣子和汤一起撈起來后 中和了咸味 
由于是现场杆制作的手工面 面条有嚼劲
个人推细面 口感好也滑溜溜

目前舌尖尖在新加坡开了四家分店
有兴趣的朋友 可以试试

㊗️大家 生活愉快！平安幸福 🙏.
.

image_desc: Photo by Muiee メイ on December 15, 2020. May be an image of food.
text:
マリナーラピザ🍕が食べたい旦那氏〜やっと塩漬けのアンチョビが買えたので、早速アリナーラソースを作り、ピザとパスタ🍝を作りました😂 旦那氏大満足 〜この瓶詰のアンチョビって少量でもめちゃ塩っぱい❗️Tesco ブランド値段は$6.95 NTUC finestでやっとゲットしました〜まだどんな料理に使えるか調べないと〜

今日のシンガポールも午後から大雨☂️ 
ホームベーカリーでピザ生を作り、意外に雨の日でも生地の発酵が進み、とても素晴らしい❣️

皆さん良い日を❣️Stay Safe 👍

在家做了好几次Pizza 
然而老爷一直想吃Marinara Pizza 
是加入塩漬anchovies 增添海咸味的pizza 
这里很少有卖这口味 多年前在東京的恵比寿
光顾了来自那不勒斯的pizza “da michele” 店家后
老爷一直对Marinara pizza 味道 唸唸不忘
前几天在NTUC finest 終於找到塩漬的anchovies 
先准备Marinara Sauce 先试做pizza 
剩余的sauce 就做pasta 
味道如何？加了anchovies 番茄酱很提味 
不需要太多配料 简单的pizza 只放芝士 或
只加小番茄🍅洋葱🧅 的pasta 就好吃了😋 

这几天的新加坡 午后就开始下大雨 
这几天的雨 都在打雷闪电 有点吓人 

用Bread maker 揉的面团 取出來靜置 
沒想到雨天☔️也一樣发酵的快 厲害啊 👍

㊗️大家 生活愉快！平安幸福 🙏

image_desc: Photo by Penn Pacific Denter Center-SG on December 13, 2020. May be an image of 1 person.
text:
6 common myths of gum disease

1.     Gum disease is not that common. On the contrary, gum disease is extremely common.

 

2.      I don't have cavities so I can't have gum disease. Cavity-free doesn’t ensure you are in the clear where gum disease is concerned.

 

3.      Having gum disease means I will lose my teeth. Not so! You don’t have to lose any of your teeth to gum disease if you practice good oral hygiene.

 

4.      Bleeding gums during pregnancy is normal. While it’s true that some women develop a condition known as “pregnancy gingivitis,” it’s not true that everyone experiences this.

 

5.      Bad breath can be an indicator of gum disease. Persistent bad breath or a bad taste in your mouth can be an indicator of gum disease and other oral diseases so it is important that you uncover what’s causing the problem.

 

6.      I have diabetes and therefore I will also have gum disease. If you have diabetes, you are at greater risk of developing some oral health problems, including gum disease, but it can be controlled so it's important that you are extra diligent with your oral health.

image_desc: Photo by 🍀🌻🌸Juewee🌸🌻🍀 on December 11, 2020. May be an image of food.
text:
🌈There are dark days in every life, but it is very rare that we cannot find some small delight to give us hope, a glimmer of light that penetrates the cloud and reminds us of the hidden radiance. 🌈 It has been a while since I do Foodart and I wanted to paint some Christmas/winter related picture, probably because the weather is so hot and I’m missing winter Japan! Also, I wanted to find a word to sum up the year: Gratitude. (Coincidentally, it matches well with the quote of the day!) I remembered many years ago, an ex-boss first shared with me about the importance of being grateful, which I couldn’t relate/understand at that time but kept the conversation in mind. After all, I was still at a very YOLO stage in life. As I get older, especially with what’s happening around us, I think now I share his sentiments well. Staying grateful is so important because it motivates us during rough moments, perseveres us through and humbles us at our best moments. While YOLO gives us the courage to pursue our dreams, having gratitude sustains us on the journey. That’s my thoughts now. ❤️❤️❤️ TGIF. 🌻

image_desc: Photo by 🍀🌻🌸Juewee🌸🌻🍀 on December 09, 2020. May be an image of strawberry.
text:
🌻The rarest feeling that ever lights a human face is the contentment of a loving soul.🌻 Yesterday I hosted a mini Christmas tea party in my house with Pizza Hut and the pizzas and honey baked wings were amazing! However, I felt something was lacking - maybe it’s because I didn’t get to eat my favourite Supreme Chicken with stuffed crust Pizza (strange that children only like to eat Four Cheese and Hawaiian pizzas 🤷🏻‍♀️) and I would love to eat more honey baked wings (too paisay to fight with kids over the wings). Today I kept thinking about the Pizza Hut meal yesterday and in the end, I gave in to my cravings! 😬 So, I ordered an expensive Pizza Hut delivery for myself - a personal pan Chicken Supreme with stuffed crust Pizza and 6 honey baked wings. 🤩🤩🤩 It has been a while since I enjoyed my lunch thoroughly (after being on medication for a while). Now I feel full and contented. Self care is self love. ❤️❤️❤️ 😘😘😘
Pairing with chamomile tea and rose petals.

お家にクリスマスツリー🎄を飾れないが、ライトアップて雰囲気を作りました💫🌟✨ここ数年クリスマス時期はほぼ海外に過ごすのがメインで、お家にクリスマス飾りが数少ない…😅 何かあるかなぁ…海外で持ち帰りの記念品を探すと〜

text:
We attended a wedding at @bijansg today. 
At Phase 2 of #circuitbreakersg , buffet style is not possible so all dishes are served at the table. The number of attendees are restricted and the volume of chatter are lower. Nevertheless, the wedding is still grand. Those who are present are grateful for each other's company at the event and spot familiar faces from the crowd. With the technology today, you can still share your moment with your loved ones, near or far.
Our prayers and blessings go to all that are celebrating their special day this #december2020 
Stay safe!

Happy Thursday friends! Introducing another super duper easy #invitationtoplay set up! S was beginning to lose interest in her sea animal toys so Mummy gave these poor creatures a new life by freezing them! 😀 Add a tinge of blue food colouring to impersonate the deep blue sea and Voila! S was inspired to “interact” with them again! Woo Hoo! During play time Mummy used the opportunity to introduce names of these sea animals! 😀

Try this with any toys your little ones have lost interest in and see the magic!! Do include sensory materials like handy scoopers/water beads to develop fine motor skills during your sensory play! Most importantly, have loads of fun and create memories! 

Materials: 
Frozen toys
Blue food colouring 
Water beads 
Sensory tools (check highlights)

image_desc: Photo by Mei Lin on December 02, 2020.
text:
November 2020 - Emerging out from a long "5-day MC" with our dear daughter. It's a reminder of #circuitbreakersg and it was quite painful - stressful home enviroment where work, play, sleep all mixed up again.
.
So I spent pockets of time to tidy up my memorabilia that I've kept away for years. As my husband @alexwong3261 reminds me, "I buy, I keep, and I throw or give away." 🙄 Well, a disclaimer is that I can't bear to throw anything! Just hoarding and hoarding until I decide what to do with them.
.
Took this stained glass marine-themed showpiece out, gave them a good wash, and found this little note I wrote to commemorate my first visit to the @kaiyukan_japan in Osaka - 10 years ago!!?? Anyway, it's sitting nicely in my cupboard. Will show and tell to Ada one of these days when she's less grabby and destructive 😅
.
#hoarder #marinebiodiversity #marinebiologist #marineaquarium #Osaka #Kaiyukan #glassware

text:
#throwbackto #april2020 #circuitbreakersg

As Coronavirus conquered the world fast and furious, Singapore went into "remote mode" in early April; in the need to break the spread. Schools stopped; businesses halted or transited to working from home; while the essential workers still headed out to serve. No one was allowed to head out, unless really necessary; this was in fact worst than confinement after giving birth. Aw man!

As per said, kiddos at home; and school learning became home-based learning; that would mean busy busy day in day out. so much monitoring to do with all of them. It's a blessing in disguise that I ain't working; i dunno how i could have coped with all the school work monitoring while still needing to WFH.

2 weeks into circuit breaker already, aside from completing work provided by her school, the vainpot was as if doing a fashion parade everyday; wearing different outfits daily; especially dresses she which she wasn't allowed to wear to school; mostly dresses by @dolliesclosetbyashley . Perks for staying home ya. 😅

#劉家小姐 #我家闺女 
#aureleiarainie #霓霓
#dolliesclosetbyashley

text:
Giving a plain jade a trendy spin?

A friend pass me a piece of jade and asked me to give it a fresh breathe of life as a gift.... I thought for a very long time and couldn't come up with a suitable design until now....so viola!

This 18 inch princess cut necklace is paired with fresh water flat square baroque pearls, a dash of citrines and accessorised with a couple of gold leaves. The focal is a carved jade depicting a monkey sitting on a giant peach 😆.


We are pledging 20% to @HPHPcommunity and @Mettacats_and_Dogs_sanctuary,  for every piece sold, DM for details.
